Axes based xpath syntax:
========================
   1)Parent to Child
      Find the parent using relative xpath
	  parent xpath/child tagName
	ex://form[@id='login']/p  
       
   2)Child to Parent
      Find the child using relative xpath
	  childxpath/parent::parent tagName
	  ex: //label[text()='Username']/parent::p
	     //input[@class='inputLogin']/parent::p
	  childxpath/..
	 ex://input[@class='inputLogin']/.. 
	 

   3)GrandParent to GrandChild
     Find the grandparent using relative xpath
	 grandparent xpath//grandchild tagName
ex:	 //form[@id='login']//input

   4)GrandChild to GrandParent
   Find the grandchild using relative xpath 
    grandchild xpath/ancestor::ancestor tagname
ex:	//input[@class='decorativeSubmit']/ancestor::form

   5)Find by Elder sibling
      Find the younger sibling using relative xpath
	  younger xpath/preceding-sibling::elder-tagName
	  //input[@id='username']/preceding-sibling::label
	  
   6)Find by using Younger sibling
      Find the elder using relative xpath
	   elder xpath/following-sibling::younger tagName
ex:	   //label[text()='Username']/following-sibling::input
       
   7)Find by using Elder Cousin
      Find the younger using relative xpath
	  younger xpath/preceding::elder-tagName
	  //input[@class='decorativeSubmit']/preceding::input
    
   8)Find by using Younger Cousin	
      Find the elder using relative xpath
	    elder xpath/following::younger tagName
ex:		//label[text()='Username']/following::input























   